<body>
  <header>
        <h1>Call of Duty: Modern Warfare</h1>
    </header>
    <section>
        <h2>Game Overview</h2>
        <p>Call of Duty: Modern Warfare is a first-person shooter video game developed by Infinity Ward and published by Activision. Released in 2019, it serves as a soft reboot of the Modern Warfare sub-series.</p>
        
        <h2>Storyline</h2>
        <p>The game follows a fictional conflict involving a terrorist organization and a CIA operative, as well as a British special forces unit. Players engage in various missions across the globe, tackling themes of war, terrorism, and morality.</p>
        
        <h2>Gameplay Mechanics</h2>
        <p>Modern Warfare features a mix of single-player and multiplayer modes. The gameplay emphasizes tactical combat, with players able to use a variety of weapons and equipment. The game also introduces new mechanics such as a more realistic damage system and the ability to mount weapons for better accuracy.</p>
        
        <h2>Multiplayer</h2>
        <p>The multiplayer mode includes various game types and maps, allowing players to engage in team-based combat. It also features a progression system, allowing players to unlock new weapons and customization options.</p>
    </section>
    <footer>
</body>

<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Call of Duty: Black Ops</h1>
    </header>
    <section>
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>Call of Duty: Black Ops is a first-person shooter video game developed by Treyarch and published by Activision. It was released in November 2010 and is the seventh installment in the Call of Duty series.</p>
        
        <h2>Storyline</h2>
        <p>The game is set during the Cold War era and follows a CIA operative named Alex Mason, who is tasked with uncovering a conspiracy involving a mysterious numbers station. Players experience various missions across different locations, including Cuba, Vietnam, and the Soviet Union.</p>
        
        <h2>Gameplay Mechanics</h2>
        <p>Black Ops features a variety of gameplay mechanics, including a robust multiplayer mode, customizable loadouts, and a unique currency system for purchasing weapons and equipment. The game also introduced the popular Zombies mode, where players can team up to fight against waves of undead enemies.</p>
    </section>
    <footer>
    
</body>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Call of Duty: Warzone</h1>
    </header>
    <section>
        <h2>Game Overview</h2>
        <p>Call of Duty: Warzone is a free-to-play battle royale game released in March 2020. It is part of the Call of Duty franchise and is set in the fictional city of Verdansk.</p>
        
        <h2>Storyline</h2>
        <p>Warzone features a narrative that intertwines with the events of Call of Duty: Modern Warfare. Players engage in combat as they fight to be the last person or team standing in a large-scale battle.</p>
        
        <h2>Gameplay Mechanics</h2>
        <p>The game supports up to 150 players in a single match, with various modes including solo, duo, and squad play. Players can find weapons, equipment, and vehicles throughout the map, and the gameplay emphasizes strategy and teamwork.</p>
        
        <h2>Key Features</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Large open-world map with diverse environments</li>
            <li>Cross-platform play</li>
            <li>In-game currency system for purchasing items</li>
            <li>Regular updates and seasonal content</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
